MISSIONARY FLIGHTS INTERNATIONAL
IMPORTANT INFORMATION
Your crew welcomes you aboard MISSIONARY FLIGHTS INTERNATIONAL. You
are flying aboard a Douglas DC-3 Airliner, the world's finest and most respected
transport aircraft. Your Captain has met the skill and experience requirements
established by the U.S. Government for all airline pilots, as well as specific profi-
ciency standards in the operation of a Douglas DC-3
Every effort has been made to eliminate the chance of an emergency situation.
We do ask, however, that you take a moment to study this card to become
familiar with this aircraft for your comfort and safety.
SEAT BELTS
During all takeoffs and landings, your
seat belt should be securely fasten-
ed. The SEAT BELT signs will advise
you when
you should
fasten your
seat belt. We do recommend that you
leave your seat belt on at all times
while seated.
Seat backs are to be in
the upright position during takeoffs

PRO-

CRAFT.
EMERGENCY EXITS
Three emergency exits are available
to the passengers on our DC-3 - two
window exits on either side of the
cabin at the rear of the wing and the
main
cabin
airstair
door
which you entered.
through

not tamper
with them
unless
an
emergency situation exists.
LAVATORY
The restroom door is on the left as
you face the rear of the aircraft. USE
ONLY THIS DOOR! Remain clear of
all other doors.
AIRCRAFT GALLEY
Refreshments are available from the
MFI galley. DO NOT attempt to use
the galley yourself.
Please ask a
crew member to serve you.
HELP KEEP IT CLEAN
The crew is responsible for cleaning
this aircraft after each flight.
You
can help by giving all trash to the
flight attendant for disposal.
DO
NOT place gum in ash trays or under
seats.
DO NOT use airsickness bags
for trash disposal.
